<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Letter</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="18Jul1931"><font color="red">18 July 1931</font> <i>Letters III</i> (to Stanislaus Joyce): I had offered my nephew George who is workless &pound;1 a week if he would help me with my notes from 2 to 5 pm every day but his stepmother (he is 21) took from him the <i>Exagmination</i> &hellip; etc etc &hellip; The affair as you know is clear as mock turtle. Having eloped with my present wife in 1904 she with my full connivance gave the name of Miss Gretta Greene &hellip; but &hellip; see Hargreave&apos;s Laws of England page 471-2 </div>
